HEADWORD: Phlebogram
<hw>Phleb"o*gram</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fle`ps</grk>, <grk>flebo`s</grk> + <ets>-gram</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A tracing (with the sphygmograph) of the
movements of a vein, or of the venous pulse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

